    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Knockout of Thorase Increases AMPAR Surface Expression and AMPAR Currents\"\n\nFig.3: \"Deficits in Homeostatic Synaptic Scaling and Endocytosis of AMPARs in Thorase KO neurons\"\n\nFig.4: \"NMDA-induced AMPAR Internalization is Reduced in an ATPase-Dependent Manner in Thorase KO Neurons\"\n\nFig.6: \"Thorase Deficiency Enhances AMPAR Currents and LTP and Impairs LTD Without Affecting Basal Synaptic Transmission at CA1 Hippocampal Synapses\"\n\nDiscussion: \"In contrast, Thorase acts at GluR2-GRIP1 complexes to control the endocytosis and removal of AMPARs from the postsynaptic membrane. The identification of Thorase as a major regulator of AMPAR trafficking offers new opportunities to enhance the understanding and to identify additional regulators of AMPAR turnover.\". Experimental description: - \"Conditional Thorase knockout (KO) mice were generated...\"",
